title: Warning Channel 07: East + CM BSOIC --> red (after today's software update)
text: Earlier on swing shift, G. Brown rebooted SIOC:BSY0:PP01 as part of planned work to add EPICS readback for the BSOICs that tie into the new S29 BSOIC PLC. Looks like the Warning Channel faulted after the IOC came back up. Garth had indicated that OK status signals for new neutron BSOIC may have been crossed (0-OK, 1-Fault instead of the expected reverse enumeration). I suspect that this may be the case for the one of the neutron BSOICs that tie into S29 BSOIC PLC. After Garth successfully connected the BSOICs to the channel, this neturon BSOIC with reversed signals probably faulted the warning channel. Unfortunately, I am unable to find any control system statuses on the BSOICs that report to S29 BSOIC PLC or any statuses on the PLC itself. The associated Alarm Channel 11 is green and has been since before the work was started. The Warning response procedure has not yet been updated to reflect that more statuses are inputting to this channel now, but we followed it anyway. It lists three BSOICs are connected to this channel: -BSOBSY04 is OK. -BSOBTW04 and BSOBTW05n are both bypassed since the LCLS Secure Loop is Latched. This fault does not present a safety hazard as the Alarm Channel is still active and green, so we will know if there is an actual BSOIC fault. This Warning channel is just intended to let us know that the BSOICs listed are not outside their warning limits. Instead of relying on this Warning overnight, we will rely on the Alarm and monitor the BSOIC statuses via strip tool. Will CATER and then notify ADSO and connect with Garth regarding a fix in the morning.
